translation: All the warriors appeared absorbed in warfare in the battle-field, and Vishnu caused the death and fall of the enemy.12.

translation: Then he placed all the four Vedas on the protruding part of his teeth and caused the death and fall of the persistent inimical demons;

transliteration: Daibrahm Aagyaa Dhanur Bed Keeyan|| Sabhai Santnantaan Ko Soukh Deeyan||
translation: Vishnu commanded Brahma and he created the Dhanur-veda for the happiness of all the saints.13.
In this way, the sixth partial incarnation of the Visnu manifested himself,

gurmukhi: sBY dust ijqy kIXo byd auDwrM ]
transliteration: Sabhai Doust Jite Keeyo Bed Udhaaran||
translation: Who destroyed the enemies and protected the Vedas;
There was the victory of Dharma (righteousness) and the gods collectively were Victorious,
And they caused to remove the pride of all in a right way.14.

transliteration: It(i) Sribachittra Naatake Chhevaan Avtaar Bairaah||6||
translation: End of the description of the sixth BOAR INCARNATION in BACHITTAR NATAK.6.
Now begins the description of Narsingh Incarnation:
Let Shri Bhagauti Ji (The Primal Lord) be helpful.
